message.content: Papilio anchisiades is a species of butterfly found in parts of South and Central America. It has a wingspan of 90-120 mm. The upper surface of its wings is mostly black, with a yellow band and iridescent blue-green markings. The undersides of the wings are brown with yellow spots. Its body is black with white spots. It has long, slender antennae and 6 legs. The larvae feed on plants within the citrus family. The species is commonly found in tropical forests and other wooded areas.
